text: Hurricane Earl was a tropical cyclone in the Caribbean Sea and Gulf of Mexico in August 2016. The storm struck Belize and Mexico with winds of around 80 mph. The storm caused 13 deaths in the Dominican Republic. More than fifty other deaths took place, mostly in Mexico. Damage totaled over $115 million. ==References== Category:August 2016 events Category:Hurricanes in Mexico Category:2010s in Mexico Category:21st century in the Dominican Republic Category:2010s in Belize Category:2016 Atlantic hurricane season Category:Category 1 Atlantic hurricanes
